Preheat your oven to 200°C. Halve the @bell pepper{2}(halved lengthways) and remove the core and seeds. Lay, cut-side up on a lightly oiled #baking tray{} and set aside. Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces. Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{163%g} in a #sieve{}. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}. Pull the @basil{6%leaves} from their stalks, (discard the stalks).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the shallot. Fry until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}, then add the @dried Italian herbs{1/2%tsp}, sweetcorn and @steamed basmati rice{1/2%portion}. Stir and cook for another ~{2%minutes}, breaking up the rice with a #wooden spoon{}.

Pour the @tomato passata{1/2%cup} into the pan along with a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Tear in half the basil leaves, stir together and cook for another ~{2%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat and stir through half the grated cheddar. Use a #spoon{} to fill the hollowed-out peppers with the rice filling, pressing it in tightly so you can use as much filling as possible!

> TIP: Any left over filling can be served on the side if you like.

Drain the @mozzarella{1} and cut two slices per person from it. Place a slice on top of each pepper half, then sprinkle on the remaining grated cheese. Season each pepper half with a little @black pepper{} then bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden and bubbly, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, slice the remaining mozzarella and the @medium tomato{2}(sliced). Arrange the mozzarella and tomato slices on a #plate{} then drizzle with a glug of @olive oil{} and the @balsamic vinegar{6%tbsp}. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper then tear the remaining basil leaves over the top.

Serve the veggie stuffed peppers alongside the caprese salad. Enjoy!